<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>myrtifolia</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>manzanita</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>viscida</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Eriodictyon</i> <i>californicum</i>, <i>Frangula</i> <i>californica</i> ssp. <i>tomentella</i>, <i>Heteromeles</i> <i>arbutifolia</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>scoparius</i>, <i>Quercus</i> <i>berberidifolia</i> and <i>Quercus</i> <i>wislizeni</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Pinus</i> <i>attenuata</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>sabiniana</i> or <i>Quercus</i> <i>chrysolepis</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 2 m; canopy is intermittent to
continuous. Herbaceous layer is sparse. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Arctostaphylos myrtifolia</i> > 30% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Wood and Parker 1988).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Low hills. Soils are coarse, very acidic, nutrient-poor soils with cement-like with yellow crusts of iron oxide.  </div>
</div>

        
