<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Seeds of <i>Arctostaphylos myrtifolia </i>germinate with heat from fire. Stands require periodic fire to maintain current species composition. Infrequent fire results in tree encroachment, shrub decline, and seed bank decline. Frequent fire tends to convert the stands to grassland. Intermediate periods between fires will best maintain the alliance (Swiecki and Bernhardt 2003).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (30-100+ years)
				
